tatistics and criticism.</p>\r\n<p>If you have questions contact Angel Bobo at 209-496-5292 or Jessica Herd at 850-274-5649 or by email <a href=\"mailto:jessicaherd@hotmail.com\">jessicaherd@hotmail.com</a></p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>',163,'2011-11-13 19:45:00','2011-11-13 22:00:00',0,NULL,NULL,0,1,0,0,0,0,1,'2011-11-11 23:52:23',99,1,255,255,'0','',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL),(102,0,5,6,'group','Teen Summit (hosted by STARS/AAWCS)','Jake Gaither Community Center','',139,'2011-10-12 18:00:00','2011-10-12 20:00:00',0,NULL,NULL,0,5,0,0,0,50,1,'2011-10-09 19:08:09',98,1,255,255,'0','',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL),(103,0,7,0,'profile','12th Annual Freaks & Geeks with Seminole State College','Heathrow, Florida','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"><span id=\"internal-source-marker_0.8065603857394308\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Freaks & Geeks is an event centered on the Digital Media industry and encompasses aspects of art, entertainment, and communication. This is the 12th year that Seminole State College has sponsored this student-centered event. Freaks & Geeks will be held this year on Friday, November 11, 2011 beginning at 6pm and running until about 11pm. The event will begin with the unveiling of our 2011 Student Digital Arts Show and will include guest speakers, live demonstrations, graphics and networking competition, gaming and other interesting events that are put on by our sponsors.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The principle idea behind Freaks & Geeks is to give our students exposure to the Digital Media and IT industry, network with professionals who are working in the field, and mainly to just have fun. Other than education in a classroom, we feel there is nothing more important than getting our students connected to the people that make the Digital Media field so exciting.</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Previous participants in the event have included Channel 13, EA Sports, Disney Feature Animation, Bright House Networks, Dell, Florida Interactive Entertainment Academy (FIEA), Orlando Advertising Federation, Create Magazine, Gigabits LAN Center, MindComet, Digital Media Alliance Florida, Seminole County Woman, DRMP, Timber Creative Group, Glitch Gaming, Qdoba, Play and Trade Games, Planet Digital, Studio Glue Photography, OPEC, Digitec Interactive, KJS Designs, Jessiedee Inc., PrintXPress, Gizmo Productions, Pizza Hut,  and many more. This year we would like to feature even more live demonstrations and guest speakers along with a real focus on the gaming industry—the true beginning of the Freaks & Geeks event.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"><span id=\"internal-source-marker_0.8065603857394308\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This is truly a wonderful event that is aimed at enhancing our student’s knowledge of the industry as well as providing many networking opportunities for them. If We hope to see you there.</span></div>\r\n</span></div>\r\n</span></p>',332,'2011-11-11 18:00:00','2011-11-11 23:00:00',0,NULL,NULL,2,5,0,1,0,0,1,'2011-10-12 05:27:30',102,1,28.7728,-81.3714,'0','',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL),(104,0,6,25,'group','Webinar with CEO of Thycotic Jonathan Cogley','CPCC Central Campus LT Building Rm 4134','<p><span><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\">STARS in STEM - The Premiere Student Organization for  students interested in  Science,  Technology, Engineering & Math Careers is hosting a live Webinar  with Guest Speaker Jonathan Cogley CEO and founder of Thycotic on  Thursday, October 13th.<br /> <br /> Thycotic offers two major services, a Secret Server software and a  Password Reset Server but they are also one of the biggest agile  programming training facilities located in Washington DC.  This is an  amazing networking opportunity for summer internships and possible  employment.  The topic of discussion will be Agile Programming Concepts  in the Software Development Cycle.  Join us in a live Webinar as  Jonathan Cogley discusses the principles and techniques that many  software development companies are implementing.<br /> <br /> When: Thursday October 13th  5pm-6pm<br /> Location: CPCC Central Campus LT Building Room 41