e University, Portland, OR','<p>ChickTech is a nonprofit organization dedicated to creating cool,  exciting technology events for girls and women. We’re tired of seeing  women not realize their potential in the high tech industry, and we’re  out to change it!</p>\r\n<p>ChickTech: High School is here to show girls that engineering can be fun and exciting!</p>\r\n<p>Hosted at Portland State University January 26-27, 2013, we will  offer an array of workshops for them to choose from in an action-packed  weekend. It will be an exclusive event, with only 100 sophomore and  junior girls chosen to participate. 9 high schools will be selected from  the Portland, Oregon, area in mid-July 2012, with 10 girls chosen from  each school. The remaining 10 spaces will be reserved for alternative  education girls, including homeschooled teens.  We will also put on a  “Tech Show” at the end of the weekend, where our participants can show  off what they’ve created to friends, family, sponsors, and each other.</p>\r\n<p>Learn about our <a href=\"http://www.chicktech.org/participants/workshops/\" title=\"Workshops\">hands-on workshops</a>!</p>\r\n<p>Join our mailing list to be notified of milestones, specific needs, and progress. Interested in volunteering? <a href=\"http://www.chicktech.org/contact/\" title=\"Contact\">Contact us</a>!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tentative Event Schedule</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>January 26<sup>th</sup></strong></p>\r\n<p>9:00am-9:30am: Registration</p>\r\n<p>9:30am-10:00am: Keynote speaker, discussion, and move into workshops</p>\r\n<p>10:00am-12:00pm: Workshop session</p>\r\n<p>12:00pm-1pm: Lunch – time to talk with mentors and peers + make USB  bracelet (split into two groups: 30 min for lunch, 30 min for bracelet)</p>\r\n<p>1pm-4pm: Workshop session</p>\r\n<p>4pm-4:30pm: Talk with mentors, wrap up</p>\r\n<p>Transportation leaves at 5pm</p>\r\n<p><strong>January 27<sup>th</sup></strong></p>\r\n<p>9:00am-9:15am: Arrive</p>\r\n<p>9:15am-9:45 Keynote, discussion and move to workshops</p>\r\n<p>9:45am-12:00pm: Workshop session</p>\r\n<p>12:00pm-1pm: Lunch</p>\r\n<p>1pm-3:45pm: Workshop session</p>\r\n<p>3:45pm-4:00/4:15pm: Set up for Tech Show</p>\r\n<p>4:00pm-5:30pm: Tech Show (with sponsors, friends, family, mentors), raffle for prizes</p>\r\n<p> </p>',626,'2013-01-26 09:00:00','2013-01-27 17:30:00',0,NULL,NULL,0,1,0,0,0,10,0,'2012-11-13 20:22:17',271,1,45.5118,-122.684,'-8','ChickTech is a nonprofit organization dedicated to creating cool, exciting technology events for girls and women.',0,'','0000-00-00',1,1),(216,0,4,20,'group','Meeting - 12/07/2012','NWFSC P110','<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Tahoma; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\">At this meeting, we\'ll discuss how we\'ll bring our Galaga project to fruition. This will include assessing the skills we have at our disposal, getting a comprehensive list of the materials we need, and getting a general feel for how we\'ll be going about it.</span></p>',862,'2012-12-07 10:00:00','2012-12-07 12:00:00',0,NULL,NULL,0,1,0,0,0,0,0,'2012-12-03 23:14:13',145,1,255,255,'-6','Second and last meeting of the semester',0,'','0000-00-00',0,0),(217,0,8,3,'group','SPARCS - Techno Club','McClintock Middle School, Charlotte, NC','',77,'2013-01-09 18:00:00','2013-01-09 19:00:00',0,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-01-09 16:55:16',3,1,35.181,-80.767,'-5','Weekly outreach at the McPie Family Night, each Tuesday. Team Leaders - Ebony Martin and Francisco Guadalupe Vargas',0,'weekly','2013-05-07',1,1),(218,217,5,3,'group','SPARCS - Techno Club','McClintock Middle School, Charlotte, NC','',77,'2013-01-15 18:00:00','2013-01-15 19:00:00',0,NULL,NULL,0,0,1,0,0,0,0,'2013-01-09 16:55:16',205,1,35.181,-80.767,'-5','Weekly outreach at the McPie Family Night, each Tuesday. Team Leaders - Ebony Martin and Francisco Guadalupe Vargas',0,'weekly','2013-05-07',1,1),(219,217,5,3,'group','SPARCS - Techno Club','McClintock Middle School, Charlotte, NC','',77,'2013-01-22 18:00:00','2013-01-2