king computers apart and reassembling',1,'','0000-00-00',1,1),(259,0,5,3,'group','BAM Minority Student Day (BMSD)','Microsoft Charlotte Campus','<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal;\">NOTE: Exact times TBD. Check back often for updates.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12pt; font-size: 13.333333969116211px;\">--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\r\n<div><strong style=\"font-size: 13.333333969116211px;\">From Tiffany Kirkland:</strong></div>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal;\"> </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 30px;\">My name is Tiffany Kirkland and I am a Technical Account Manager at Microsoft Charlotte and one of the Co-chairs for Blacks at Microsoft (BAM).  <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12pt; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 30px;\"><strong><br /></strong>I’m reaching out to you to invite you and your students to support yet another great volunteer opportunity to help Microsoft reach tomorrow’s future by promoting career opportunities within the field of technology.<strong> <br /><br /></strong>In support of Microsoft’s commitment to enabling broad access to technology to any person from any background, BAM will be hosting hosts its annual <strong>BAM Minority Student Day (BMSD)</strong> on <strong>Friday, February 15<sup>th</sup></strong> at the Microsoft Charlotte Campus.  The goals of this event are to:<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Wingdings;\">³<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> </span></span>Build and maintain relationships with students from minority and under-represented populations</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Wingdings;\">³<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> </span></span>Expose students who attend schools with limited resources to diversity at Microsoft in various professions, educational backgrounds and cultures</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Wingdings;\">³<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> </span></span>Present information to students to encourage them towards continued education post high school</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Wingdings;\">³<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> </span></span>Encourage students to learn about the opportunities that can lead to a career in the field of technology</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Wingdings;\">³<span style=\"font-size: 7pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> </span></span>Provide an opportunity for students to learn about emerging technologies that Microsoft is developing</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 30px;\">To help us achieve these goals, BAM would like to engage volunteer resources from UNCC’s Department of Computer Science to deliver a <strong><em>Game Lab Session</em></strong>.  Last year I volunteered to assist with the Digi Girlz Camp and supported the Game Lab Session taught by two graduate students from UNCC and I was truly impressed with their delivery as well as impressed with how excited the students were to learn how to create their own games.  If possible, BAM would like to provide this same opportunity and experience to the students who participate in Minority Student Day.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 30px;\"> </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12pt; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; padding-left: 30px;\">Please let me know if there are students in your department who would be willing volunteer their time to deliver a <strong><em>Game Lab Session</em></strong> and help us inspire students to embrace the many of opportunities within the field of technology.</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12pt; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal;\">--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12pt; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal;\">We will get you the same content that was delivered last year. You will be responsible for learning the content and delivering an exciting and engaging activity it at the event. Alternatively, you can create your own activity if you\'d like; feel free to discuss that option with Scott.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12pt; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal;\"> </p>',77,'2013-02-15 00:00:00','2013-02-15 23:59:59',0,NULL,NULL,0,1,2,0,0,0,0,'2013-01-16 20:27:09',307,1,255,255,'-5','Deliver a Game Lab Session to learn how to create their own games.',1,'','0000-00-00',1,1),(260,0,5,3,'group','Ten80 Student Racing Challenge','West Charlotte High School, Charlotte, NC','<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>IMPORTANT: Contact Jeannie Ruiz (<span style=\"color: #555555; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.333333969116211px; line-height: normal; white-space: nowrap;\">findjeannie@gmail.com</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">) if you would like to volunteer. Please CC Scott (sheggen@uncc.edu) and Karen (karen.bean@uncc.edu) when you contact Jeannie.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\r\n<p>Through the Ten80 Student Racing Challenge: NASCAR STEM Initiative, we prepare for a future as engineers, scientists, business, marketing and creative professionals.</p>\r\n<p>Our team is like a mini professional motorsports team. We compete using a 1:10 scale electric radio controlled (RC) car. Like motorsports industry professionals, we are rewarded for managing and marketing our team, for creatively using our assets and talents, and winning races through engineering a strong, fast and efficient car and team.</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p>We can compete and collaborate with other student teams around the United States via the internet and face-to-face.</p>\r\n<p>1. <span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><strong>Points Race</stron